name: Stanislav Zaitsev
headline: Unity Developer – Innopolis University
creator: False
bio:
Меня зовут Станислав, и я занимаюсь разработкой игр и приложений. Мой путь в этой области начался еще в студенческие годы. Я постоянно изучаю и развиваюсь в сфере создания приложений на движке Unity. Мои проекты в основном связаны с VR/AR-разработкой, но также я занимался разработкой приложений для мобильных и десктопных устройств.

Ссылки:
- Мой Telegram: https://t.me/Rutherfordum
- Канал в Telegram: https://t.me/Pro_XR
- Мой сайт-визитка: https://sites.google.com/view/proxr/main

Мои навыки и знания:
- Работа с системой контроля версий Git, предпочтительно SmartGit GUI, но также уверенное использование терминала.
- Использование фреймворков и плагинов UniTask, UniRX, R3, Zenject, VContainer, Entitas, LeoECS для разработки в Unity.
- Опыт разработки клиент-серверных приложений.
- Работа с WebRTC для установления однорангового соединения между устройствами для передачи видео, аудио и текстовых сообщений в реальном времени с низкой задержкой для устройств HoloLens 2, Android, iOS и Windows.
- Соблюдение принципов ООП, SOLID, DRY, KISS, YAGNI и др.
- Верстка UI с использованием стандартной системы Unity и UIToolKit.
- Написание тестов с использованием Unity Test Framework, NUnit.
- Опыт работы с графикой в Unity, написание шейдеров с использованием ShaderGraph, URP, HDRP.
- Оптимизация приложений с использованием инструментов Profiler и FrameDebugger.
- Опыт сборки и публикации приложений в Google Play и App Store.
- Опыт сборки для XR-устройств: HoloLens 2, Meta Quest 1-3, Pico 4, AR Mobile, PC VR.

Научные статьи:
- ИНТЕРАКТИВНОЕ ПРОГРАММИРОВАНИЕ РОБОТОТЕХНИЧЕСКИХ МАНИПУЛЯТОРОВ НА ОСНОВЕ ОЧКОВ HOLOLENS 2 https://elibrary.ru/item.asp?id=46309109

- ПРОГРАММА ДЛЯ УПРАВЛЕНИЯ РОБОТАМИ UR НА ОСНОВЕ ROS https://elibrary.ru/item.asp?id=47783344

- ПРОГРАММНАЯ МОДЕЛЬ ВИЗУАЛИЗАЦИИ ПРОГРАММЫ ПРОМЫШЛЕННОГО РОБОТА ДЛЯ СИСТЕМ ИНТЕРАКТИВНОГО ПРОГРАММИРОВАНИЯ РОБОТОВ https://elibrary.ru/item.asp?id=47783774

name: Manuel Mazzara
headline: Professor of Software Engineering
creator: False
school_1: Alma Mater Studiorum – Università di Bologna
school_2: Alma Mater Studiorum – Università di Bologna
bio:
I am a software engineer interested in the application of formal techniques to build reliable software.

Specialities:
Software Engineering
Formal Methods
Concurrency
Deployment of formal methods in industry

The work conducted by Manuel Mazzara and his team in recent years focuses on the development of theories, methods, tools and programs covering the two major aspects of software engineering: the process side, describing how we develop software, and the product side, describing the results of this process.

name: Ilya Afanasyev
location: St Petersburg, St Petersburg City, Russia
headline: Robotics Institute
creator: True
school_2: Baltic State Technical University "VOENMEH" named after D.F. Ustinov
bio:
* PhD in engineering.
* 6+ years in project, product & people management.
* 20+ years of R&D experience in both academy and industry for HW & SW development.
* 8+ years in teaching (as a professor).
* Reviewer for IEEE T-ASE, IEEE RA-L, IFAC, IEEE CASE, IEEE Access, MDPI Sensors.
* Expertise: Sensors and Measurements. Mobile Robotics. Computer Vision. Intelligent Transportation Systems. Human-Computer Interaction. Experimental Physics.
* More than 120 publications in English and Russian (including 55 papers indexed in Scopus). 3 patents.
* Scopus h-index 13 (55 papers, 730+ citations, www.scopus.com/authid/detail.uri?authorId=57202156203),
* RSCI h-index 13 (84 papers, www.elibrary.ru/author_items.asp?authorid=146105),
* Google Scholar h-index 19 (120 papers, 1400+ citations, https://scholar.google.ru/citations?user=Ogv_bdYAAAAJ).
* IEEE Member #94806215
* 20+ years experience with tools & sensors (incl. 3D & 2D cameras, lasers, Kinect, rangefinders, PEMs, SEMs, microphones, hydrophones, multicamera systems & optical sensors), including sensor calibration, experimental testing, signal processing, data treatment and validation, etc.
* SW: MATLAB, Python, MathCAD, 3ds Max, OpenERP, MS Project.
* HW, equipment & instruments: Heat and vacuum chambers, TestBeds, Stands, Generators, Oscilloscopes, LEDs, UV lamps, isotopes, synchrotron facilities, thermocouples, contact sensors, Radiometers, UV/X-ray spectrometers, PCB, analog & digital electronics, etc.
* Teaching courses in English: "Sensors & Sensing" (2016-2023),  "Sensing, Perception & Actuation" (2019-2022), "Intelligent Mobile Robotics" (2017-2019), "Mobile Robotics and Autonomous Driving" (2019), "Control Theory" (2016-2019), “Sensation and Perception” (2018), "System Identification & Simulation" (2017), "Theoretical Computer Science" (2017).

name: Rais Khadeev
headline: IT Brand Manager | DevRel | Employer Branding
creator: False
bio:
My name is Rais, and I have over 9 years of experience working on major Tech and Fintech projects, including roles in Innopolis, IT outsourcing companies like DataArt and Akvelon, and Rosbank.

For more than 3 years, I have been developing HR brand strategies, including launching long-term communication and reputation projects. My expertise spans fundraising, resource acquisition, running tenders, and managing budgets, with successful approvals for projects exceeding half a million USD. I have experience in planning, execution, and result analysis.

I have developed and implemented HR branding strategies, promoted EVP (Employer Value Proposition), and tailored it to various target audiences.  

My experience also includes publishing articles in various media outlets and digital publications on topics such as HR branding and IT developer expertise. I have successfully placed content in platforms like rb.ru, TpProger, Hi-Tech, and several specialized Telegram channels.

I personally participate in video interviews and podcasts and have a proven track record in organizing and producing large IT conferences. I’ve also coordinated over 200 online and offline meetups on IT, HR, and startup topics. These meetups helped my clients enhance their HR and IT branding, boost company visibility in the tech market, and leverage participants’ resources to fill vacancies. Notably, I facilitated 1-day offers and hiring days at both DataArt and Rosbank.

I have been involved in building over 15 IT and HR communities, which now include approximately 6,000 members. These communities cover a wide range of technology stacks, as well as niche topics such as smart city and smart factory initiatives.

In terms of leadership, I have over 5 years of experience as an IT Brand Lead, Head of Community, DevRel, and Customer Success Lead, managing teams and departments of up to 10 people.

I hope my skills and expertise align with your project needs.

Sincerely,  
Rais Khadeev

bio:
I am a team leader, brand director and event producer with 5+ years of experience in marketing, branding and project management. My career highlights include successfully managing design, marketing and creative projects.

My Journey 🚀

After university I heard about recruiting a team for the Russian Silicon Valley – IT-city Innopolis. And I got a job in the role of Event manager. I was designing Innopolis creativity and culture. Produced 200+ events, gathering a warm community around and inside the city.  

Next, I accepted a new challenge. I became head of marketing department at Innopolis. My major objective to assemble a team and build a strong brand for the new city that would attract investments, people and companies.

Feel free to contact with me directly on LinkedIn or drop me an email: dmurzina8@gmail.com 😊

name: Maksim Matveev
headline: Analytics and development
creator: False
bio:
Мои навыки
Бизнес и системный анализ, сбор, проектирование требований, управление требованиями
Нотации BPMN, IDEFx, UML, eEPC
Разработка технических заданий, постановка задач на разработку ПО (Use Cases, User Stories, Customer Journey Map)
Управление проектами, рисками, командой, Scrum, Agile
Экономика проекта, UNIT экономика, AARRR, продуктовые метрики DAU, MAU, Retention, LTV, NPS и др.
Проверка гипотез, A/B тестирование, HADI – циклы, провожу CustDev, UX анализ, составляю VPC, прорабатываю LC(BMC) и др.
Презентации, выступления

Мои технические навыки
Разбираюсь в статистике, применяю параметрические и непараметрические методы, Bootstrapping, Power Analysis.
Знаю Python и библиотеки Pandas, numpy, matplotlib, seaborn, работаю в Jupyter Notebook.
Знаю SQL, БД MySQL, PostgreSQL, MSSQLServer, NoSQL
Интеграционные решения: REST, SOAP, GraphQL, gRPC, Kafka
Описание интеграционного взаимодействия (Sequence Diagram, Swagger Editor)
Инструменты Microsoft Corporation (Excel, Word, Power Point, Power BI и т.д.)
Средства проектирования пользовательских интерфейсов: Figma, Creately, BalsamiqMockups и др.
Знакомы инструменты моделирования: Camunda, BPWin и др.

Инструменты для работы: Jira, Confluence, Draw.io, Lucidchart, StormBPMN, pgAdmin, DBeaver, Miro - Realtime Board, Xmind, Trello, MS Project, Soap UI, Postman, Swagger, Kibana, Zabbix, Greenshot, Notepad + +, Jupyter Notebook, Google colaboratory, Visual Studio.

bio:
TG: @PRYRAN

Всегда поддерживаю беседу, вне зависимости от темы. Умею слушать, что считаю крайне полезным навыком. Люблю возлагать на себя сложные проекты, после кропотливого труда над которым - радоваться достигнутому результату.

Поднимал распределенную файловую систему на docker swarm.

Также, стоит отметить отличный навык тайм-менеджмента, способность и желание интегрироваться в новый коллектив, выполнять сложные задачи для повышения квалификации. 
Самое важное - люблю шутить и смеяться :)
